The paper deals with the problem of finding minimum-link rectilinear paths in rectilinear polygonal domains in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. The paper presents a new algorithm for solving this problem that builds a data structure in $O(n+h\log h)$ time and answers queries in $O(\log n)$ time. The problem involves triangulating the plane, which is a common technique in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem also involves building a data structure, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem involves finding optimal solutions, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem involves dealing with obstacles, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the problem involves dealing with queries, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
